>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">

    <p class="section-label mb-4">About</p>
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-100 tracking-tight mb-10">
      Christian Dreyer
    </h1>

    <div class="prose prose-stone dark:prose-invert max-w-none space-y-6 text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400 leading-relaxed">

      <!-- Optional: add an avatar here
      <img src="/images/avatar.jpg" alt="Christian Dreyer" class="w-24 h-24 rounded-full object-cover mb-8 not-prose" />
      -->

      <p>
        <!-- Edit this section with your own bio -->
        I'm an engineer based in Norway, working primarily in fluid mechanics and thermal systems.
        My work sits at the boundary of physical modelling and computational methods — using
        simulation and data to understand systems that are difficult to study experimentally.
      </p>

      <p>
        I studied mechanical engineering at NTNU in Trondheim, where I focused on heat transfer
        and turbulence modelling. Since then I've worked on [describe your work].
      </p>

      <p>
        Outside of work, I'm interested in [your interests]. I believe that good engineering
        is as much about clear communication as it is about technical accuracy.
      </p>

      <h2>How I work</h2>
      <p>
        I try to build tools and workflows that make engineering analysis faster and more
        reproducible. Most of my day-to-day tooling is Python and Linux-based.
      </p>

      <h2>Get in touch</h2>
      <p>
        The best way to reach me is by
        <a href="mailto:christian@christiandreyer.no">email</a>.
        I'm also on <a href="https://github.com/christiandreyer" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>
        and <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/christiandreyer" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a>.
      </p>

    </div>
  </div>
</Page>
